{"name":"Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.ShrinkingLemma","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.Basic","Mathlib.Topology.MetricSpace.EMetricParacompact","Mathlib.Topology.ShrinkingLemma"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.lean#L122-L128","name":"exists_locallyFinite_iUnion_eq_ball_radius_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.html#exists_locallyFinite_iUnion_eq_ball_radius_lt","doc":"Let `R : α → ℝ` be a (possibly discontinuous) positive function on a proper metric space. Then\nthere exists a collection of pairs of balls `Metric.ball (c i) (r i)`, `Metric.ball (c i) (r' i)`\nsuch that\n\n* for all `i` we have `0 < r i < r' i < R (c i)`;\n* the family of balls `Metric.ball (c i) (r' i)` is locally finite;\n* the balls `Metric.ball (c i) (r i)` cover the whole space.\n\nThis is a simple corollary of `refinement_of_locallyCompact_sigmaCompact_of_nhds_basis`\nand `exists_iUnion_ball_eq_radius_pos_lt` or `exists_locallyFinite_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_lt`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.lean#L97-L109","name":"exists_locallyFinite_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.html#exists_locallyFinite_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_lt","doc":"Let `R : α → ℝ` be a (possibly discontinuous) function on a proper metric space.\nLet `s` be a closed set in `α` such that `R` is positive on `s`. Then there exists a collection of\npairs of balls `Metric.ball (c i) (r i)`, `Metric.ball (c i) (r' i)` such that\n\n* all centers belong to `s`;\n* for all `i` we have `0 < r i < r' i < R (c i)`;\n* the family of balls `Metric.ball (c i) (r' i)` is locally finite;\n* the balls `Metric.ball (c i) (r i)` cover `s`.\n\nThis is a simple corollary of `refinement_of_locallyCompact_sigmaCompact_of_nhds_basis_set`\nand `exists_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_pos_lt`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.lean#L78-L83","name":"exists_iUnion_ball_eq_radius_pos_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.html#exists_iUnion_ball_eq_radius_pos_lt","doc":"Shrinking lemma for coverings by open balls in a proper metric space. A point-finite open cover\nof a proper metric space by nonempty open balls can be shrunk to a new cover by nonempty open balls\nso that each of the new balls has strictly smaller radius than the old one. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.lean#L65-L72","name":"exists_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_pos_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.html#exists_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_pos_lt","doc":"Shrinking lemma for coverings by open balls in a proper metric space. A point-finite open cover\nof a closed subset of a proper metric space by nonempty open balls can be shrunk to a new cover by\nnonempty open balls so that each of the new balls has strictly smaller radius than the old one. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.lean#L55-L59","name":"exists_iUnion_ball_eq_radius_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.html#exists_iUnion_ball_eq_radius_lt","doc":"Shrinking lemma for coverings by open balls in a proper metric space. A point-finite open cover\nof a proper metric space by open balls can be shrunk to a new cover by open balls so that each of\nthe new balls has strictly smaller radius than the old one. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.lean#L42-L49","name":"exists_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_lt","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ShrinkingLemma.html#exists_subset_iUnion_ball_radius_lt","doc":"Shrinking lemma for coverings by open balls in a proper metric space. A point-finite open cover\nof a closed subset of a proper metric space by open balls can be shrunk to a new cover by open balls\nso that each of the new balls has strictly smaller radius than the old one. This version assumes\nthat `fun x ↦ ball (c i) (r i)` is a locally finite covering and provides a covering indexed by the\nsame type. "}]}